data.name: Amazon Kinesis Data Streams Service
data.description: View of key metrics relating to the health and performance of deployed Amazon Kinesis Data Streams Service.

markdown.markdownText: **Amazon Kinesis Data Streams** ![Amazon Kinesis Data Streams Service](https://icon.icepanel.io/AWS/svg/Analytics/Kinesis-Data-Streams.svg) Amazon Kinesis makes it easy to collect, process, and analyse video and data streams in real time. You can use Amazon Kinesis Data Streams to collect and process large streams of data records in real time. A typical Kinesis Data Streams application reads data from a data stream as data records. You can send the processed records to dashboards, use them to generate alerts, dynamically change pricing and advertising strategies, or send data to a variety of other AWS services. Amazon Kinesis Data Streams is part of the Amazon Kinesis streaming data platform, along with Amazon Firehose, Amazon Kinesis Video Streams, and Managed Service for Apache Flink. This dashboard is part of the out-of-box Amazon Kinesis Data Streams extension providing visibility to and alerting on key performance metrics. Details of integrations to bring in Amazon Kinesis metrics [here](https://coralogix.com/docs/cloudwatch-metricstreams-kinesis-data-firehose/)

**Use Cases Covered**

* Get Records Success (number of successful GetRecord operations per Kinesis stream measured over the specified time period)
* Get Records Throttled (number of records rejected due to throttling in a GetRecords operation on a Kinesis stream, measured over a specified time period)
* Get Records Latency (time taken per GetRecords operation, measured over the specified time period)
* Get Records Average Iterator Age (age of the last record in all GetRecords calls made against a Kinesis stream, measured over the specified time period. Age is the difference between the current time and when the last record of the GetRecords call was written to the stream)
* Get Record Bytes (number of bytes retrieved from the Kinesis stream using the GetRecord operation measured over the specified time period)
* Put Records Success (number of successful PutRecord operations per Kinesis stream measured over the specified time period)
* Put Records Latency (time taken per PutRecords operation, measured over the specified time period)
* Put Records Throttled (number of records rejected due to throttling in a PutRecords operation per Kinesis stream, measured over a specified time period)
* Put Record Bytes (number of bytes put to the Kinesis stream using the PutRecord operation measured over the specified time period)
* Read Provisioned Throughput Exceeded (number of GetRecords calls throttled for the steam over the specified time period)
* Write Provisioned Throughput Exceeded (number of records rejected due to throttling for the stream over the specified time period. This metric includes throttling from PutRecord and PutRecords operations)
* Subscribe To Shard Success (records whether the SubscribeToSHard subscription was successfully established. The subscription only lives for at most 5 minutes. Therefore, this metric gets emitted at least once every 5 minutes)
* Subscribe To Shard Event Success (emitted every time an event is published successfully)
* Subscribe To Shard Event Bytes (number of bytes received from the shard, measured over the specified time period)
* Subscribe To Shard Event Records (number of records received from the shard, measured over the specified time period)
* Subscribe To Shard Rate Exceeded (metrics emitted when a new subscription attempt fails because there already is an active subscription by the same consumer or if you exceed the number of calls per second allowed for this operation)
* Subscribe To Shard Event Millis Behind Latest (difference between the current time and when the last record of the SubscribeToShard event was written to the stream)

**More about performance monitoring of Amazon Kinesis Data Streams** [here](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/streams/latest/dev/monitoring-with-cloudwatch.html)
